172
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:39,080
So getting over someone, so I have to get over him means that I have to stop feeling
所以忘记某人，所以我必须忘记他，意思是我必须停止

173
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:41,840
so sad about what, what happened, right?
为发生的事情感到难过，对吧？

174
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:45,100
Because usually you say this when someone's sad or angry.
因为通常当某人难过或生气时你会这么说。

175
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:49,360
And also it kind of means that you have to forget or let that person go, you know, like
而且这也意味着你必须忘记或放手那个人，你知道，就像

176
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:50,360
get over it.
放下吧。

177
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:54,680
We're going to move on here to the last word in today's language takeaway, which is incorrigible.
我们要继续讲今天语言要点的最后一个词，那就是“incorrigible”。

178
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:57,760
Okay, an incorrigible person.
好的，一个无可救药的人。

179
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:59,920
Alright, incorrigible.
好的，无可救药。

180
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:00,920
What could this mean?
这可能是什么意思？

181
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:03,600
Well, let's look at the sentence where we find it.
嗯，让我们看看我们找到它的句子。

182
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:06,240
You are incorrigible.
你真是无可救药。

183
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:07,760
Gulam says this to Stephen.
Gulam对Stephen这么说。

184
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:08,760
Right.
对。

185
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:12,920
So it's an adjective and basically it means that you have no correction of some sort.
所以这是一个形容词，基本上意思是你在某种程度上无法被纠正。

186
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:15,560
Well, there's an argument between Stephen and Gulam.
嗯，Stephen和Gulam之间有一场争论。

187
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,640
So they're brothers.
所以他们是兄弟。

188
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:18,240
And Stephen says, I don't want to get married.
Stephen说，我不想结婚。

189
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,920
I don't want to marry her.
我不想娶她。

190
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:23,560
He's complaining and his brother says, you are incorrigible.
他在抱怨，他哥哥说，你真是无可救药。

191
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:25,680
You just won't stop.
你就是停不下来。

192
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:30,040
So someone's feelings, their emotions, their ideas about something, they just can't be
所以某人的感受、情绪、对某事的想法，就是无法被

193
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:31,880
changed or altered.
改变或改变。

194
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:32,880
They're fixed.
他们是固定的。

195
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:35,240
You know, this guy, he's like, I'm not going to get married.
你知道，这家伙，他就像，我不会结婚。

196
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:37,760
And his brother says, you're incorrigible.
他哥哥说，你真是无可救药。

197
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:38,880
I just can't change your mind.
我就是无法改变你的想法。

198
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:40,280
It's kind of like being stubborn.
这有点像固执。

199
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:41,960
Yeah, yeah, exactly.
是的，是的，没错。

200
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:44,300
And we hear this phrase a lot together.
我们经常一起听到这个短语。

201
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:46,680
So you're incorrigible.
所以你是无可救药了。

202
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:51,680
So this is often just kind of a, it's not an insult, but it's a way for us to kind of
所以这通常只是一种，不是侮辱，而是我们用来

203
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:54,440
be sarcastic or to make fun of someone.
讽刺或取笑别人的方式。

204
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,440
You're incorrigible, Marco.
你真是无可救药，马可。

205
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:59,240
Usually you say it when you're loud, you know, you're being nice.
通常你说这话时，是因为你声音很大，但你其实是在表现友好。

206
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:00,280
Okay, cool.
好的，酷。

207
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:03,640
So five great words in language takeaway today.
所以今天语言学习环节有五个很棒的词。

208
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:08,120
And well, before we move on and listen to the dialogue again, why don't we take a look
在我们继续听对话之前，不如先看看

209
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:10,880
at Fluency Builder?
流利度提升环节？

210
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:11,880
Fluency Builder.
流利度提升。

211
00:09:11,880 --> 00:09:12,880
All right.
好的。

212
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:17,080
So this phrase is something that parents often use and grandparents as well, because obviously
所以这个短语是父母和祖父母经常用的，因为显然

213
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:20,760
parents and grandparents, they're very proud of their children, their grandchildren.
父母和祖父母，他们为自己的孩子、孙子感到非常自豪。

214
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:25,200
So they describe something as being their pride and joy.
所以他们把某样东西描述为他们的骄傲和喜悦。

215
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,840
My pride and joy.
我的骄傲和喜悦。

216
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:29,520
So it's usually a person that's your pride and joy.
所以通常是一个人是你骄傲和喜悦的对象。

217
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,520
It could be a thing too.
也可能是一个东西。

218
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:31,640
It could be a thing.
也可能是一个东西。

219
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:33,920
His Porsche Boxster is his pride and joy.
他的保时捷Boxster是他的骄傲和喜悦。

220
00:09:33,920 --> 00:09:36,240
He goes out every morning and he washes it.
他每天早上都出去洗车。

221
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:40,080
He changes the oil, he checks the gas, checks the tires.
他换机油，检查汽油，检查轮胎。

222
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,520
So it's his pride and joy.
所以那是他的骄傲和喜悦。

223
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:42,520
All right.
好的。

224
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:44,560
It's his most valued possession.
这是他最珍视的财产。

225
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:45,880
So it always goes together, right?
所以它总是连在一起用，对吧？

226
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:47,260
My pride and joy.
我的骄傲和喜悦。

227
00:09:47,260 --> 00:09:48,260
Pride and joy.
骄傲和喜悦。

228
00:09:48,260 --> 00:09:49,260
Yeah.
是的。

229
00:09:49,260 --> 00:09:50,260
Just think of it as a phrase, pride and joy.
就把它当成一个短语，骄傲和喜悦。

230
00:09:50,260 --> 00:09:51,260
All right.
好的。

231
00:09:51,260 --> 00:09:53,920
So I'm my mother's pride and joy.
所以我是我妈妈的骄傲和喜悦。

232
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:54,920
I think you are.
我觉得你是。

233
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:55,920
All right.
好的。

234
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:58,920
So you don't know my mom.
所以你不认识我妈妈。

235
00:09:58,920 --> 00:10:00,480
All right.
好的。

236
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:02,640
So somebody's pride and joy.
所以某人的骄傲和喜悦。

237
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:07,120
So now another phrase that we took a look at, and it's a way of making conversation,
现在我们来看另一个短语，这是一种聊天的方式，

238
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:09,280
especially with a person that you haven't seen in a while.
尤其是和很久没见的人。

239
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:12,000
He said, Hey, what's new with you?
他说，嘿，你最近有什么新鲜事？

240
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,880
What's new with you?
你最近有什么新鲜事？

241
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:14,880
What's new with you?
你最近有什么新鲜事？

242
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:15,880
All right.
好的。

243
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:18,520
So this might sound a little strange because normally we say, how have you been?
这听起来可能有点奇怪，因为我们通常说，你最近怎么样？

244
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:19,520
It's been a long time.
好久不见了。

245
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:20,520
How are you?
你好吗？

246
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:22,880
But this is like, you know, it's a fluency builder phrase.
但这就像，你知道，这是一个流利度提升短语。

247
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:26,240
So it's very colloquial, it's very spoken language.
所以它非常口语化，是非常地道的口语。

248
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:29,040
This you hear often between friends or family members.
你经常在朋友或家人之间听到这个。

249
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:30,960
Hey, Marco, what's new with you?
嘿，马可，你最近有什么新鲜事？

250
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:34,320
So how do you, I would answer this by saying, oh, well, not much.
那我该怎么回答呢？我会说，哦，没什么。

251
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:36,740
Or I just bought a new house.
或者我刚买了新房子。

252
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:39,480
So basically you're asking for news from a person.
所以基本上你是在问别人有什么新消息。

253
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:40,720
I haven't seen you in a long time.
我好久没见你了。

254
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:42,400
You look, you look happy and healthy.
你看起来，你看起来开心又健康。

255
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,600
So what's new with you?
所以你最近有什么新鲜事？

256
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:44,600
Oh, I got married.
哦，我结婚了。

257
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:47,040
I got a new car.
我买了新车。

258
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:49,400
These things that you can say, these are changes in my life.
这些你可以说，这些是我生活中的变化。

259
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:50,400
All right.
好的。

260
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:53,480
And usually after somebody asks you, what's new with you?
通常别人问你“你最近有什么新鲜事？”之后，

261
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:57,120
You say something and then you usually would follow up and ask that person as well, right?
你说点什么，然后通常也会回问那个人，对吧？

262
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,600
What's new and what's new with you?
有什么新鲜事？你最近有什么新鲜事？

263
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,600
Exactly.
没错。

264
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:02,000
So, you know, I got a new house, got a new job.
所以，你知道，我买了新房子，找了新工作。

265
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,000
What's new with you?
你最近有什么新鲜事？

266
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,000
Yeah.
是的。

267
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,000
Or what about you?
或者你呢？

268
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,000
What about you?
你呢？

269
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:10,600
So it's a nice, very relaxed, informal way of asking someone for news in their life.
所以这是一个很好、非常轻松、非正式的方式来询问别人生活中的新消息。

270
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:11,600
Perfect.
完美。

271
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:12,600
All right.
好的。

272
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:13,600
What's new with you?
你最近有什么新鲜事？

273
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:14,600
What else?
还有什么？

274
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:15,600
Now, he was supposed to get married, right?
现在，他本来要结婚的，对吧？

275
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:16,600
Right.
对。

276
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:17,600
So this is news.
所以这是新闻。

277
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,600
He was supposed to get married.
他本来要结婚的。

278
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:19,600
He didn't get married.
他没结婚。

279
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:20,600
What's going on?
怎么回事？

280
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:23,400
His brother, his mother, they all want to know what's going on.
他哥哥，他妈妈，他们都想知道怎么回事。

281
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:28,360
And we find out that wedding, that girl, he just couldn't go through with it.
然后我们发现婚礼，那个女孩，他就是没法坚持到底。

282
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:30,680
So I can't, I couldn't go through with it.
所以我不能，我无法坚持到底。

283
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:31,680
Okay.
好的。

284
00:11:31,680 --> 00:11:32,680
This past tense.
这是过去时。

285
00:11:32,680 --> 00:11:36,160
So he's saying, before I came to India with this girl, I couldn't go through with it.
所以他在说，在我和这个女孩来印度之前，我无法坚持到底。

286
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:39,160
So present would be, I can't go through with it.
所以现在时是，我无法坚持到底。

287
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:41,240
And going through with what here?
这里坚持什么？

288
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:44,960
We've got it, this kind of magical, strange word, it.
我们遇到了这个有点神奇、奇怪的词，“它”。

289
00:11:44,960 --> 00:11:45,960
What could this be?
这可能是什么？

290
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:50,920
So basically, what he's saying is that he couldn't complete or maybe finish something
所以基本上，他在说他无法完成或结束

291
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:51,920
that he started.
他开始的事情。

292
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:52,920
Right.
对。

293
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:55,440
So in this case, we're talking about a relationship.
所以在这种情况下，我们在谈论一段关系。

294
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:56,440
Or marriage.
或者婚姻。

295
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:57,440
Yeah, a relationship.
是的，一段关系。

296
00:11:57,440 --> 00:12:00,560
So maybe we loved each other, but I couldn't go through with it.
所以也许我们彼此相爱，但我无法坚持到底。

297
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:02,760
I couldn't go to the finish line.
我无法走到终点。

298
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:03,760
Right.
对。

299
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:04,760
I couldn't get married.
我无法结婚。

300
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:08,800
You see that a lot when maybe in movies, two people are supposed to get married.
你经常在电影里看到这种情况，两个人本来要结婚。

301
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:13,560
They're at the altar, and all of a sudden the bride says, I can't, or she goes away
他们在祭坛前，突然新娘说，我不能，或者她哭着

302
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:14,560
crying.
走开了。

303
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:16,560
I can't go through with this.
我无法坚持这个。

304
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:17,560
Exactly.
没错。

305
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:21,000
So because she loves somebody else, so can't go through with it.
因为她爱别人，所以无法坚持到底。

306
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,000
Great.
太好了。

307
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,040
So really good phrase.
所以真是个好短语。

308
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:24,560
I can't go through with it.
我无法坚持到底。

309
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:27,580
He couldn't go through with it.
他无法坚持到底。

310
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:30,080
And we find out that, well, not such a bad thing.
然后我们发现，嗯，也不是什么坏事。

311
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:31,940
Steven, he's very popular in India.
史蒂文，他在印度很受欢迎。

312
00:12:31,940 --> 00:12:32,940
The girls love him.
女孩们都喜欢他。

313
00:12:32,940 --> 00:12:38,000
We've got a great phrase for describing having lots of girls who love you.
我们有一个很好的短语来形容有很多女孩喜欢你。

314
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,000
Right.
对。

315
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:41,960
He says there will be girls throwing themselves at you.
他说会有女孩们主动投怀送抱。

316
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:42,960
Literally?
字面意思吗？

317
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:43,960
Like, ow, that might hurt.
比如，哎哟，那可能会疼。

318
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:45,080
I can't imagine that.
我无法想象。

319
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:47,640
Like, just somebody throwing themselves at you?
就像，有人直接扑向你？

320
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:49,080
No, it's not literal.
不，不是字面意思。

321
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:52,360
It's basically saying girls are very interested in you.
它基本上是说女孩们对你很感兴趣。

322
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:55,360
Girls are so interested in you that they'll be chasing you almost.
女孩们对你非常感兴趣，几乎会追着你跑。

323
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:56,360
All right.
好的。

324
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:58,480
So many, many girls, they will follow you.
所以很多很多女孩，她们会跟着你。

325
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:00,880
They'll want to be in a relationship with you.
她们想和你谈恋爱。

326
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:01,880
They like you.
她们喜欢你。

327
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:04,840
So he's saying, listen, there are other girls.
所以他在说，听着，还有其他女孩。

328
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:05,840
Don't worry.
别担心。

329
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:07,600
Girls here, they love you.
这里的女孩，她们爱你。

330
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:08,960
And it doesn't only work with girls, right?
而且这不只适用于女孩，对吧？

331
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:11,880
I can say there'll be boys throwing themselves at you.
我可以说会有男孩们主动投怀送抱。

332
00:13:11,880 --> 00:13:12,880
Right.
对。

333
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:16,280
So this is something we say about both genders, boys and girls.
所以这是我们用来形容男女双方的，男孩和女孩。

334
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:19,600
You could say, oh, God, all the boys were throwing themselves at her.
你可以说，哦，天哪，所有男孩都对她投怀送抱。

335
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,600
I'm so jealous.
我好嫉妒。

336
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:22,800
Right.
对。

337
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:25,320
But it's only basically in a loving way, right?
但这基本上只是以爱的方式，对吧？

338
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:26,680
It can't be anything else.
不能是别的。

339
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:29,000
Like somebody's chasing you for other reasons.
比如有人因为其他原因追你。

340
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:34,360
No, this is saying that they have crushes, they have feelings, they want to be romantic.
不，这是说他们暗恋你，有感情，想浪漫。

341
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:38,960
It's not a bad thing, but sometimes it's too much attention, so it can be kind of negative.
这不是坏事，但有时关注太多，所以可能有点负面。

342
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:39,960
Yeah.
是的。

343
